The paper presents a system for acquiring, processing, and rendering panoramic light field still photography for display in Virtual Reality (VR). This involves computer graphics (cs.GR) for rendering, computer vision (cs.CV) for reconstruction, multimedia (cs.MM) for compression, human-computer interaction (cs.HC) for user experience, and information retrieval (cs.IR) for the library of panoramic light field stills.
